related_items.title: Quite an AWOL problem
description: 1 drawing. | Cartoon shows a Soviet soldier standing on the Kremlin wall holding a long strip of paper labeled "Growing List of Refugees to the West." Reflects the increasing number of persons leaving the Soviet Union and Eastern Europe for the West.  In particular, may refer to the flight of East Germans to West Berlin in the spring of 1953.

related_items.title: Frankenstein
description: 1 drawing on layered paper board : ink and white out over pencil. | Cartoon shows the monster Frankenstein, labeled "Red China," towering over the Kremlin and St. Basil's Cathedral in Moscow's Red Square. A small man stands on top of the the Kremlin roof, frightened of the threat that China represents. 1958 saw a growth in influence that China held over Communist countries, for example, Yugoslavia.
